Step1: goto policies create a new policy by any name and choose service as ebs and select all action and choose All resources in resouces.
Step2: Goto IAM-master-role and attach the newly created policy  and AmazonEBSCSIDriverPolicy
Step3: follow the same steps in IAM-Worker-role from step1 to step2 and then reboot all the master and worker instances.
Step3:curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kubernetes-sigs/aws-ebs-csi-driver/master/deploy/kubernetes/secret.yaml > secret.yaml
# Edit the secret with user credentials # not required at the moment
step4: kubectl apply -f secret.yaml
Step5:kubectl apply -k "github.com/kubernetes-sigs/aws-ebs-csi-driver/deploy/kubernetes/overlays/stable/?ref=release-1.5"
Step6: kubectl apply  -f storage-class.yaml
step7:kubectl apply  -f tomcat-pvc.yaml
step8:kubectl get pv
step9:kubectl get pvc
